cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CL

The paper deals with the use of low-precision ADCs in millimeter wave MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed methods also exploit the sparsity of the channel, which is a common theme in signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper presents a low-complexity detection method based on belief propagation, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and natural language processing (cs.CL).
